	<entry>
		<string>Many modules are basically dealing with the equivalent of real-life objects, like news articles, projects, surveys, race tracks or whatever.</string>
		<translation></translation>
		<references>
			<reference file="modules/dynamicdata/xartemplates/admin-main.xd" line="24" />
		</references>
	</entry>
	<entry>
		<string>Those &quot;objects&quot; each have a number of &quot;properties&quot;, like an item id, a title, an author, a deadline or a number of VIP places, and their data is generally stored in some dedicated module table.</string>
		<translation></translation>
		<references>
			<reference file="modules/dynamicdata/xartemplates/admin-main.xd" line="29" />
		</references>
	</entry>
	<entry>
		<string>The whole management of the object instances (creation, modification, display, deletion, ...) is typically hard-coded in the module, and tightly wired to the underlying data structure, which makes it difficult to e.g. add another property to your objects without rewriting half the module code (and templates).</string>
		<translation></translation>
		<references>
			<reference file="modules/dynamicdata/xartemplates/admin-main.xd" line="34" />
		</references>
	</entry>
	<entry>
		<string>The Dynamic Data module allows you to dynamically add properties to your module objects, and to integrate them with the rest of the site without much effort - regardless of whether you're the module developer, a third-party solution designer or the website admin.</string>
		<translation></translation>
		<references>
			<reference file="modules/dynamicdata/xartemplates/admin-main.xd" line="39" />
		</references>
	</entry>
	<entry>
		<string>And no-one says you're limited to existing modules - you could just as easily create whole new objects by defining their properties and telling the Dynamic Data module where their data should be coming from : dedicated module tables, dynamic data fields (auto-generated), some utility module from Xaraya or a user function you'll specify.</string>
		<translation></translation>
		<references>
			<reference file="modules/dynamicdata/xartemplates/admin-main.xd" line="44" />
		</references>
	</entry>
